t: "They ask you ňĻfor a ruling, O Prophetňļ. Say, ‚ÄúAllah gives you a ruling regarding those who die without children or parents.‚ÄĚ If a man dies childless and leaves behind a sister, she will inherit one-half of his estate, whereas her brother will inherit all of her estate if she dies childless. If this person leaves behind two sisters, they together will inherit two-thirds of the estate. But if the deceased leaves male and female siblings, a male‚Äôs share will be equal to that of two females. Allah makes ňĻthisňļ clear to you so you do not go astray. And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"